    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-11-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-11-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="378"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d378">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.5123/2365</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Egyptian Minister</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ratib Bey</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <p>The Secretary of State presents his compliments to the Honorable the Minister of
                    Egypt and, with further reference to a memorandum which the Chargé d’Affaires
                    left at the Department on September 27, 1935, concerning the taxation of certain
                    securities owned by the Egyptian Government and deposited in a bank in New York,
                    quotes below an excerpt from a letter from the Governor of the State of New
                        York:<note n="22" xml:id="d378fn22">Dated October 28, 1935.</note>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The Commissioner of Taxation and Finance advises me that you may assure
                            the Egyptian Chargé d’Affaires that the State of New York has no tax
                            which expressly or by implication taxes the French Government Dollar
                            Bonds as property, or the income therefrom, or the transfer thereof,
                            under the circumstances set forth in your communication.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-02">November 2,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
